cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MA 

The paper deals with game theory and optimization in wireless networks, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics), as the paper explicitly introduces a novel framework based on repeated games. The second likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper deals with power control in distributed small cell wireless networks. The third likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper discusses the optimization of system performance. The fourth likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper deals with the interactions of different transmit base stations. The fifth likely category is cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), as the paper deals with cooperative power control.
